The paper deals with stochastic optimization for expected risk minimization with random perturbation, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization. The paper discusses algorithms for this problem and provides theoretical analysis and experimental results on logistic regression and AUC maximization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
